node.text: In a tribute to the beloved movie "Field of Dreams," Kevin Costner — who portrayed Ray Kinsella, a farmer who builds a baseball field in his cornfield that attracts ghosts of baseball greats — started off the night by walking through the cornfield surrounding the stadium. ⚾️ "30 years ago, on the other side of that corn we filmed a movie that stood the test of time," Costner said. "Tonight, thanks to that enduring impact that little movie had, it's allowed us to come here again...There is probably just one more question to answer – is this heaven? Yes it is," he added, a nod to one of the film's famous quotes. 📷: Frank Micelotta/Fox Sports/Picturegroup/Shutterstock, Universal
